A fast way to generate half-decent documentation from the source is
via epydoc (an improvement on happydoc).
See /packages/src/python/Packages/epydoc/epydoc-2.0-docs for more info
or the webpage at http://epydoc.sourceforge.net/

We recommend the html documentation.

position yourself in the NX root directory (where you can see
CVS/  Doc/  Examples/  NX/  README  Tools/  setup.cfg  setup.py)

Then do:

epydoc -o ./Doc/pdf -v --inheritance listed -n NX --pdf NX

to generate a pdf documantation file in ./Doc/pdf/api.pdf
and

epydoc -o ./Doc/html --css blue --private-css green -v --inheritance \
listed -n NX NX

to generate html documentation in ./Doc/html/index.html

(Note that all options must preceed the list of modules)
